<p>I am working on a test project to learn symfony2/twig. All I want to do is display a list of images, determined by a location. </p>  <p>I am retrieving data for these images from Instagram's API. The API sends back JSON data. For each image there is a wealth of information. I just need the low_resolution values to place in image tag.</p>  <p>I know how to transverse the data using standard PHP. However, I have no idea how to do this using TWIG. I just want to display the low_resolution url in an image tag. The closet I got was the following:</p>  <pre class="lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>{% if images_array == true %}         {% for key,value in images_array %}             {{ value.link }}              {% for key,value in value.images %}                 &lt;div class="col-md-3"&gt;                     &lt;img src="{{ value.url }}" alt="" class="thumbnail img-responsive" /&gt;                                    &lt;/div&gt;             {% endfor %}          {% endfor %}     {% endif %} </code></pre>  <p>The problem with the above is that it loops through all the [url] in the [images] instead of displaying the value from [low_resolution]</p>  <p>Below is the first index of the data being brought in from Instagram.</p>  <pre><code>Array (     [0] =&gt; Array         (             [attribution] =&gt;              [tags] =&gt; Array                 (                     [0] =&gt; dubai                 )              [location] =&gt; Array                 (                     [latitude] =&gt; -29.854119007                     [name] =&gt; ICC Durban Exhibition Centre,Durban,South Africa                     [longitude] =&gt; 31.029556697                     [id] =&gt; 450025614                 )              [comments] =&gt; Array                 (                     [count] =&gt; 0                     [data] =&gt; Array                         (                         )                  )              [filter] =&gt; Normal             [created_time] =&gt; 144